@{
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<style>
    .privacy-container {
        max-width: 1200px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 60px 20px;
        color: #333;
    }

    .privacy-header {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 50px;
    }

        .privacy-header h1 {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            color: #2c3e50;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            font-weight: 700;
        }

        .privacy-header p {
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            color: #7f8c8d;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }

    .privacy-section {
        margin-bottom: 40px;
        background: #fff;
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 30px;
        box-shadow: 0 2px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
    }

        .privacy-section h2 {
            color: #3498db;
            font-size: 1.8rem;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            padding-bottom: 10px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
        }

        .privacy-section h3 {
            color: #2c3e50;
            font-size: 1.3rem;
            margin: 25px 0 15px 0;
        }

        .privacy-section p, .privacy-section ul {
            line-height: 1.8;
            color: #555;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .privacy-section ul {
            padding-left: 20px;
        }

        .privacy-section li {
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }

    .last-updated {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 50px;
        font-style: italic;
        color: #95a5a6;
    }

    @@media (max-width: 768px) {
        .privacy-container {
            padding: 30px 15px;
        }

        .privacy-header h1 {
            font-size: 2rem;
        }

        .privacy-section {
            padding: 20px;
        }
    }
</style>

<div class="privacy-container">
    <div class="privacy-header">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p>Your privacy is important to us. This policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you use our medicine donation platform.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="privacy-section">
        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We collect information to provide better services to all our users. The types of information we collect include:</p>

        <h3>Personal Information</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Contact details (name, email address, phone number)</li>
            <li>Demographic information (age, gender, location)</li>
            <li>Identification documents for verification purposes</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Non-Personal Information</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Browser type and version</li>
            <li>Pages visited on our site</li>
            <li>IP address and general location data</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="privacy-section">
        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>To facilitate medicine donations and requests</li>
            <li>To verify donor and recipient identities</li>
            <li>To improve our services and user experience</li>
            <li>To communicate with you about your account or transactions</li>
            <li>To detect and prevent fraud or misuse of our platform</li>
            <li>To comply with legal obligations</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="privacy-section">
        <h2>3. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
        <p>We do not sell your personal information. We may share information with:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Verified NGOs and healthcare providers for medicine distribution</li>
            <li>Service providers who assist with platform operations</li>
            <li>Legal authorities when required by law</li>
        </ul>
        <p>All third parties are contractually obligated to maintain confidentiality and security.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="privacy-section">
        <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
        <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your data:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Encryption of sensitive data</li>
            <li>Regular security audits</li>
            <li>Access controls and authentication procedures</li>
            <li>Secure server infrastructure</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="privacy-section">
        <h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>You have certain rights regarding your personal information:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Right to access and receive a copy of your data</li>
            <li>Right to correct inaccurate information</li>
            <li>Right to request deletion of your data</li>
            <li>Right to withdraw consent</li>
            <li>Right to lodge complaints with data protection authorities</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="privacy-section">
        <h2>6. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
        <p>We use cookies and similar technologies to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Remember your preferences</li>
            <li>Analyze site traffic and usage patterns</li>
            <li>Improve our services</li>
        </ul>
        <p>You can control cookies through your browser settings.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="privacy-section">
        <h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this policy periodically. We will notify you of significant changes through our website or email.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="privacy-section">
        <h2>8. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have questions about this privacy policy or your personal data:</p>
        <p>
            Email: privacy@medidonate.org<br>
            Phone: +1 (800) 123-4567<br>
            Address: 123 Health Avenue, Medical City, MC 12345
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="last-updated">
        <p>Last updated: @DateTime.Now.ToString("MMMM dd, yyyy")</p>
    </div>
</div>